ðŸ“… Add a Slicer for Quarter (Filter All Visuals)
Add a slicer visual.

Drag Quarter field to Values.

To affect all visuals:

Slicer will auto-filter visuals on the same page (if model relationships exist).

ðŸ·ï¸ Format the Bar Chart to Show Data Labels
Select the chart.

Go to Format pane.

Expand Data Labels, turn it On.

Customize font size, color, position if needed.

ðŸ“ˆ Use Line Chart to Show SalesAmount Over Quarters
Insert Line Chart.

Drag Quarter to Axis.

Drag SalesAmount to Values.

ðŸ–±ï¸ Add Tooltip to Show Product Details on Hover
Create a tooltip page:

Add a new page â†’ Set Page Information â†’ Tooltip = On.

Add visuals (e.g., table of Product info).

Set Page Size â†’ Tooltip under Format pane.

On your main visual:

Go to Format â†’ Tooltip â†’ Choose Report Page.

Select the tooltip page you just made.

ðŸ” Sync Slicers Across Pages
Select slicer â†’ Go to View â†’ Sync Slicers.

A pane opensâ€”check the pages where the slicer should sync.

Choose whether to sync and/or make visible.

âš¡ Create a Custom Visual with Dynamic Measure Selection (Sales vs. Profit)
Create a table of measures:

DAX

Metrics = DATATABLE("Measure", STRING, {{"Sales"}, {"Profit"}})
Create a slicer using Metrics[Measure].

Create a dynamic measure:

DAX

SelectedMetric =
SWITCH(
    SELECTEDVALUE(Metrics[Measure]),
    "Sales", [Total Sales],
    "Profit", [Total Profit]
)
Use SelectedMetric in your visuals.

ðŸ§­ Implement Hierarchy: Region > Product > Quarter Drill-Down
In Fields pane, drag Product under Region, and Quarter under Product to create a hierarchy.

Add hierarchy to visualâ€™s axis.

Use drill icons (expand all / go to next level).

ðŸ“š Use Bookmarks to Toggle Between Two Visuals
Add two visuals in the same position (e.g., Line chart & Bar chart).

Create two Bookmarks:

One with Visual 1 shown, Visual 2 hidden.

One with Visual 2 shown, Visual 1 hidden.

Add Buttons and assign actions via Action â†’ Bookmark.

